 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Cotransaction Architecture — Atomic Phase Transitions Across the Knowledge Pipeline (INV-HARVEST-007, INV-STORE-001, INV-BILATERAL-001). BACKGROUND: The stale session bug (Session 031) revealed a structural gap: phase transitions in the knowledge pipeline are implemented as sequential events with gaps between them, and lifecycle invariants that depend on both sides of the gap are fragile. In an append-only CRDT with no global clock, the only mechanism preserving boundary integrity is CO-LOCATION in the same transaction. The cotransaction principle: when event A necessarily implies event B, they share a transaction. Five pipeline boundaries need atomic transitions: (1) Harvest↔Session (highest priority — causal prerequisite for all others), (2) Observe↔Crystallize (structured observations auto-crystallize), (3) Spec↔Task (new specs auto-generate implementation tasks), (4) Trace↔Witness (new code→spec links auto-generate FBW skeletons), (5) Close↔Verify (already partially implemented via CBV). The ultimate vision: universal observe — braid observe becomes the single entry point where agents say what they know and the cotransaction engine routes to correct pipeline layers automatically. PHASING: Phase 1: Harvest-session cotransaction (foundation, unblocks all others). Phase 2: Observe-crystallize cotransaction (highest UX impact). Phase 3: Spec-task + trace-witness cotransactions (pipeline acceleration). Phase 4: Universal observe (full vision). Phase 5: Lifecycle verification layer L(t) (secondary monitoring). AXIOLOGICAL ALIGNMENT: SEED.md §5 (bounded conversation lifecycle), SEED.md §6 (reconciliation taxonomy — TEMPORAL divergence), ADR-GUIDANCE-002 (basin competition — ceremony elimination makes Basin A invisible). ACCEPTANCE: (A) Harvest atomically rotates sessions. (B) Structured observations auto-crystallize. (C) New specs auto-generate tasks. (D) Traces auto-generate witness skeletons. (E) No lifecycle boundary gaps. TRACES TO: INV-HARVEST-007, INV-STORE-001, INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-TASK-006, INV-WITNESS-001, INV-GUIDANCE-014."
